<Docs title="Quick Start" description="Get productive with omegon in 5 minutes.">
  <h1>Quick Start</h1>

  <h2>1. Install</h2>
  <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://omegon.styrene.dev/install.sh | sh</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Authenticate</h2>
  <pre><code># API key (Anthropic or OpenAI):
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."

# Or OAuth (Claude Pro/Max):
omegon login</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Start a Session</h2>
  <pre><code># Interactive mode (default):
omegon

# One-shot prompt:
omegon --prompt "explain this codebase"

# Resume last session:
omegon --resume</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Key Commands</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>/effort</code></td><td>View or change inference tier (Servitor → Omnissiah)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/context</code></td><td>Inspect context class routing state, pin floor</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/providers</code></td><td>Show provider auth status and routing summary</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/dashboard</code></td><td>Toggle the live TUI dashboard overlay</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/cleave</code></td><td>Decompose and parallelize a complex task</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>/init</code></td><td>Initialize project memory and orientation</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>5. Project Memory</h2>
  <p>
    Omegon automatically builds a persistent knowledge layer for your project.
    Facts, decisions, and patterns survive across sessions. The agent uses
    <code>memory_store</code>, <code>memory_recall</code>, and <code>memory_query</code>
    tools to maintain context continuity.
  </p>
  <p>
    Memory is stored in <code>.pi/memory/</code> in your project directory.
    The <code>facts.jsonl</code> file is tracked in git for cross-session portability.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Design Tree</h2>
  <p>
    The design tree is a markdown-based knowledge graph in <code>docs/</code>.
    Each node has a status lifecycle: <code>seed → exploring → resolved → decided → implementing → implemented</code>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The agent uses <code>design_tree</code> and <code>design_tree_update</code> tools
    to explore, decide, and track implementation of architectural decisions.
  </p>
</Docs>
